22#ifndef GCC_COMMON_TARGET_H
23#define GCC_COMMON_TARGET_H
24
25
26/* Sets of optimization levels at which an option may be enabled by
27 default_options_optimization. */
28enum opt_levels
29{
30 OPT_LEVELS_NONE, /* No levels (mark end of array). */
31 OPT_LEVELS_ALL, /* All levels (used by targets to disable options
32 enabled in target-independent code). */
33 OPT_LEVELS_0_ONLY, /* -O0 only. */
34 OPT_LEVELS_1_PLUS, /* -O1 and above, including -Os and -Og. */
35 OPT_LEVELS_1_PLUS_SPEED_ONLY, /* -O1 and above, but not -Os or -Og. */
36 OPT_LEVELS_1_PLUS_NOT_DEBUG, /* -O1 and above, but not -Og. */
37 OPT_LEVELS_2_PLUS, /* -O2 and above, including -Os. */
38 OPT_LEVELS_2_PLUS_SPEED_ONLY, /* -O2 and above, but not -Os or -Og. */
39 OPT_LEVELS_3_PLUS, /* -O3 and above. */
40 OPT_LEVELS_3_PLUS_AND_SIZE, /* -O3 and above and -Os. */
41 OPT_LEVELS_SIZE, /* -Os only. */
42 OPT_LEVELS_FAST /* -Ofast only. */
43};
44
45/* Description of options to enable by default at given levels. */
46struct default_options
47{
48 /* The levels at which to enable the option. */
49 enum opt_levels levels;
50
51 /* The option index and argument or enabled/disabled sense of the
52 option, as passed to handle_generated_option. If ARG is NULL and
53 the option allows a negative form, the option is considered to be
54 passed in negative form when the optimization level is not one of
55 those in LEVELS (in order to handle changes to the optimization
56 level with the "optimize" attribute). */
57 size_t opt_index;
58 const char *arg;
59 int value;
60};

62#define DEFHOOKPOD(NAME, DOC, TYPE, INIT) TYPE NAME;
63#define DEFHOOK(NAME, DOC, TYPE, PARAMS, INIT) TYPE (* NAME) PARAMS;
64#define DEFHOOK_UNDOC DEFHOOK
65#define HOOKSTRUCT(FRAGMENT) FRAGMENT
